"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136020","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-07-04","<p>In line with European Society of Cardiology guidelines, a transthoracic cardiac echo is used to detect significant structural (such as the various cardiomyopathies) and electrophysiological abnormalities (such as abnormal QT syndromes and Brugada syndrome) in Army recruits.</p><p>This follows a review of the recruit's full clinical history, a full clinical examination and electrocardiogram (ECG).</p><p>RAF and Royal Navy recruits undergo a similar screening process but without an ECG. This is in line with American College of Cardiology guidelines.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2019-07-04T15:19:33.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136020/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136020/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136020/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-07-01","Armed Forces: Heart Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 1 July 2019 to Question 269662 on Armed Forces: Heart Diseases, what criteria clinicians follow when seeking to detect significant structural and electrophysiological abnormalities in recruits.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","271441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136021","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-07-09","<p>The Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport does not offer a payroll deduction facility to be used for joining a credit union service. There are currently no plans to introduce one.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2019-07-09T14:39:35.747Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136021/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136021/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136021/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-07-01","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport,  whether his Department offers employees a payroll deduction service to enable staff to join a credit union; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","271326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136022","Department for Education","false","2019-07-09","<p>Although the department does not offer employees a specific payroll deduction service to enable staff to join a credit union, we offer consolidated voluntary deductions from pay for subscriptions and premiums as well as a Give As You Earn scheme to enable employees to make tax-free donations to charities through payroll.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2019-07-09T15:07:54.083Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136022/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136022/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136022/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-07-01","Department for Education: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether his Department offers employees a payroll deduction service to enable staff to join a credit union; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","271327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136023","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-07-09","<p>The Department does not currently offer a payroll deduction service that enables staff to join a credit union and at present has no plans to do so.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2019-07-09T15:54:54.073Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136023/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136023/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136023/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-07-01","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs,  whether his Department offers employees a payroll deduction service to enable staff to join a credit union; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","271328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136024","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2019-07-08","<p>I can confirm my department currently does not have the facility to allow staff to join a credit union through payroll deductions. Staff can still make arrangements to contribute to a credit union via direct debit.</p><p> </p>","Spelthorne","Kwasi Kwarteng",,"2019-07-08T15:42:48.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136024/answer","Biography information for Kwasi  Kwarteng","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136024/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1136024/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2019-07-01","Department for Exiting the European Union: Credit Unions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union,  whether his Department offers employees a payroll deduction service to enable staff to join a credit union; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","271329"
