m universal credit for non-universal credit debts are not repaying their debts.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","270705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1135485","Cabinet Office","false","2019-07-02","<p>Ministers and officials meet frequently with external officials to discuss a wide range of electoral issues.</p><p>Details of external meetings by Ministers and Permanent Secretaries are published quarterly and are available on gov.uk.</p><p> </p>","Torbay","Kevin Foster","270810","2019-07-02T14:50:29.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1135485/answer","Biography information for Kevin Foster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1135485/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1135485/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-06-28","European Parliament: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what discussions he has had with the Electoral Commission on the potential disenfranchisement of EU citizens resident in the UK in the European Parliament elections.","false","Biography information for Mohammad Yasin","Bedford","Mohammad Yasin","270809"
