"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134810","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-07-02","<p>The Government has taken a number of steps to increase employers’ awareness of their legal obligations to pregnant employees. This has included working with ACAS to develop comprehensive advice and guidance and updating the content on the GOV.UK website. The Government’s recent consultation on pregnancy and maternity discrimination also asked how effective the current approach is in helping employees and employers to understand their rights and obligations. We will be publishing the Government response in due course.</p><p>The Equality Advisory and Support Service advises and assists individuals on issues relating to equality and human rights, across England, Scotland and Wales. Where an employer fails to meet its obligations, a pregnant employee can seek redress through an employment tribunal.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst","269739","2019-07-02T14:09:42.793Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134810/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134810/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134810/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-06-26","Employment: Pregnancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that employers meet their legal obligations to pregnant employees.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","269738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134811","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-07-02","<p>The Government has taken a number of steps to increase employers’ awareness of their legal obligations to pregnant employees. This has included working with ACAS to develop comprehensive advice and guidance and updating the content on the GOV.UK website. The Government’s recent consultation on pregnancy and maternity discrimination also asked how effective the current approach is in helping employees and employers to understand their rights and obligations. We will be publishing the Government response in due course.</p><p>The Equality Advisory and Support Service advises and assists individuals on issues relating to equality and human rights, across England, Scotland and Wales. Where an employer fails to meet its obligations, a pregnant employee can seek redress through an employment tribunal.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst","269738","2019-07-02T14:09:42.843Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134811/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134811/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1134811/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-06-26","Employment: Pregnancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what action will be taken against employers who do not meet their legal obligations to pregnant employees.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","269739"
